ZH: 顶多，我每个星期只能去一次游泳池。
EN: At most, I can only go to the swimming pool once a week.

ZH: 这本书我顶多看到第五章。
EN: I've only read up to the fifth chapter of this book at most.

ZH: 我们公司顶多只雇佣五十个员工。
EN: Our company employs at most fifty employees.

ZH: 他顶多能坚持跑三公里。
EN: He can at most run three kilometers.

ZH: 明天顶多有五个人参加会议。
EN: At most, there will be five people attending the meeting tomorrow.

ZH: 我顶多只会弹一首钢琴曲。
EN: I can only play one piano piece at most.

ZH: 这个解释很拗口，顶多只能理解一半。
EN: This explanation is too convoluted, I can only understand half of it at most.

ZH: 我顶多只能逗猫玩半小时。
EN: I can only play with the cat for half an hour at most.

ZH: 顶多，这个任务需要四个小时完成。
EN: At most, this task will take four hours to complete.

ZH: 这件事顶多只需要三步就能解决。
EN: This problem can be solved in only three steps at most.

ZH: 她顶多只会说几句简单的中文。
EN: She can only speak a few simple Chinese sentences at most.

ZH: 这件衣服顶多只能穿一次。
EN: This piece of clothing can only be worn once at most.

ZH: 顶多，这本书只需要一个小时就能读完。
EN: At most, this book can be read in one hour.

ZH: 这个电池顶多只能使用一天。
EN: This battery can only last for one day at most.

ZH: 我顶多只能等你五分钟。
EN: I can only wait for you for five minutes at most.

ZH: 这个电视节目顶多只有五分钟。
EN: This TV show is only five minutes long at most.

ZH: 顶多，我能陪你去一个小时。
EN: At most, I can accompany you for one hour.

ZH: 这个问题顶多只需要十分钟解决。
EN: This problem can be solved in only ten minutes at most.

ZH: 我顶多只会唱一首歌。
EN: I can only sing one song at most.

ZH: 这个任务顶多只需要两个人完成。
EN: This task can be completed by only two people at most.
